<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2015/02/02/springone2gx-2014-replay-working-with-databases-and-groovy">SpringOne2GX 2014 Replay: Working with Databases and Groovy</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon news-and-events"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/news">News and Events</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/c910c2f6520a5977a836d74e86e07cb4?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Pieter Humphrey</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2015-02-02 13:56:00.0">February 2, 2015</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="1954" href="/blog/2015/02/02/springone2gx-2014-replay-working-with-databases-and-groovy#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Recorded at SpringOne2GX 2014.</p>
<p>More Groovy Track</p>
<p> Slides: <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/databases-withgroovy-paulkingoct2013">http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/databases-withgroovy-paulkingoct2013 </a></p>
<p>This talk reviews the features in Groovy which make it easy to work with databases. It reviews the features of Groovy SQL including Groovy's LINQ-like lazy evaluation technology called datasets. In addition, it looks at working with a couple of NoSQL databases: MongoDB (using GMongo) and Neo4J (using it's Java api and via Gremlin support).</p>
<p> <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Y8PV1tlw0Vk" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe> </p>
</div>
</section>
